      <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Section 1 title" --><!-- InstanceEndEditable --></p>
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Section 1" -->
<p>The term "the cloud" has been thrown around in so many different venues and with such a variety of meanings, from applications to storage to development, that it is almost impossible to understand what it is, let alone define it. While "cloud" can be (and is) all of these things, its flexible nature  is  such that it can be difficult to determine where to leverage it in your existing infrastructure to adequately meet and support business needs. </p>
<p><a
 href="http://ed-link.techtarget.com/r/30J2XQ7/XNBFW/75TWZ9/STUE5/LCYGX/DD/h?a=6483467"
>Check out this white paper</a> for a back-to-basics  look at cloud computing and discover how your business can benefit from one of  the many cloud products currently available. Learn the differences between various cloud platforms, explore the recent evolution of  virtualization and cloud technologies and more. Also get in-depth knowledge on:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cloud &ndash; what it is and what it isn&rsquo;t        </li>
<li> Public vs. private cloud </li>
<li>Best practices for cloud management</li>
<li>And more </li>
</ul>
<p>Get to the bottom on "the cloud" once and for all with this<a
 href="http://ed-link.techtarget.com/r/30J2XQ7/XNBFW/75TWZ9/STUE5/6FOQ8/DD/h?a=6483467"
> vendor-neutral guide</a> to cloud computing.      </p>
